33. J Pak Med Assoc. 2018 Mar;68(3):466-468.Metaplastic breast cancer: A case report.Surenkok S(1), Tahberer E(2), Cinkaya A(2), Kodaz H(3), Deger A(4).Author information: (1)Acibadem University, Vocational School of Health Services.(2)Department of Radiation Oncology, Acibadem Hospital.(3)Department of Medical Oncology, Acibadem Hospital.(4)Department of Pathology, Dumlupinar University, Turkey.Metaplastic carcinomas of the breast are very rare and constitute less than 0.5% of all breast cancers. Breast metaplastic carcinomas are aggressive.They haveworse prognosis compared to other breast cancers. We present a case diagnosedwith metastatic breast cancer due to the rare occurrence of these tumours intreatment of which surgical chemotherapy, radiotherapy and hormonotherapy areemployed together.PMID: 29540888 